@startuml
title Auth service — Discord OAuth2 & session flow

actor User
participant "Browser" as Browser
participant "Frontend (SvelteKit)" as Frontend
participant "Auth Service (Axum)" as Auth
participant Discord
database "Postgres (users)" as Postgres
storage "Redis (sessions)" as Redis

User -> Browser: clicks "Login"
Browser -> Frontend: view / (click)
Frontend -> Auth: GET /discord/login
Auth -> Discord: 302 Redirect to OAuth2 authorize (client_id, redirect_uri, state)
Browser -> Discord: User authorizes (OAuth2 UI)
Discord -> Browser: Redirect to /discord/callback?code=...&state=...
Browser -> Auth: GET /discord/callback (code)
Auth -> Discord: POST /token (exchange code for token)
Discord --> Auth: access_token, refresh_token
Auth -> Auth: encrypt tokens (TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY -> 32-bytes HEX -> AES-GCM)
Auth -> Discord: GET /users/@me (with access_token)
Discord --> Auth: user_info (id, username, avatar...)
Auth -> Postgres: INSERT/UPDATE users (upsert by discord_id)
Auth -> Redis: CREATE session (session_id -> user_id, encrypted tokens, ttl)
Auth --> Browser: Set-Cookie session_id; Redirect to FRONTEND_URL
Browser -> Frontend: request with cookie
Frontend -> Auth: GET /me (cookie)
Auth -> Redis: GET session:{session_id}
alt session found
  Auth -> Postgres: SELECT user by id
  Auth --> Frontend: 200 OK { user profile }
else session missing/expired
  Auth --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized
end

Frontend -> Auth: GET /refresh (optional)
Auth -> Redis: validate session, refresh TTL or rotate session/token
Auth --> Frontend: 200 OK (new session info)

Frontend -> Auth: GET /logout
Auth -> Redis: DEL session:{session_id}
Auth --> Frontend: 204 No Content; Clear cookie

note over Auth: AppState holds `Config`, `PgPool`, `redis::Client`, `oauth2::reqwest::Client`
note over Auth: CORS origin = FRONTEND_URL (set in src/main.rs)

@enduml
